            "Baltimore Ravens",

        "story": "MIAMI GARDENS, Fla. --  <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3916387/lamar-jackson\">Lamar Jackson</a> returned for the <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/team/_/name/bal/baltimore-ravens\">Baltimore Ravens</a>, and so did the chants of M-V-P!  on the road.\n\n\r\n              Jackson threw for 204 yards and four touchdowns, showing little rust in his return from a right hamstring strain, and the Ravens routed the <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/team/_/name/mia/miami-dolphins\">Miami Dolphins</a> 28-6.\n\n\r\n              The two-time MVP completed 18 of 23 passes in his first start since Week 4 against Kansas City, and the Ravens (3-5) won their second straight as they hope to make a run in the wide-open AFC North.\n\n\r\n              It felt great, Jackson said. I didnt have any problems. I was feeling good out there.\n\n\r\n              Tight end <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3116365/mark-andrews\">Mark Andrews</a> made two touchdown catches. Jackson's other TD passes went to tight end <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4241263/charlie-kolar\">Charlie Kolar</a> and receiver <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4360939/rashod-bateman\">Rashod Bateman</a>.\n\n\r\n              <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3043078/derrick-henry\">Derrick Henry</a> rushed 119 yards on 19 carries. Jackson ran the ball five times for 14 yards.\n\n\r\n              Jackson connected on his first nine passes of the second half before he finally missed <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/15795/deandre-hopkins\">DeAndre Hopkins</a> on a deep throw in the final minute of the third quarter. The game was out of reach by then, and Jackson had already thrown for his fourth TD  <a href=\"https://x.com/NFL/status/1984083574925263316\">a 9-yard toss to Bateman</a> that put Baltimore up 28-6.\n\n\r\n              Its do or die, Jackson said. Win or go home. Usually we start off winning games. But right now were behind, and weve all got to step it up.\n\n\r\n              The Ravens were 1-5 just five days ago but have put together consecutive impressive wins after <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4035671/tyler-huntley\">Tyler Huntley</a> led them to a 30-16 victory over Chicago last Sunday.\n\n\r\n              We had two games that we needed to win in four days, Baltimore coach John Harbaugh said. And they were absolute must-wins. And for our guys to step up the way they did ... is commendable. And it just means were two games under .500. Thats all it means. But were two games under .500, right? We were four games under .500.\n\n\r\n              <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4241479/tua-tagovailoa\">Tua Tagovailoa</a>, who completed 25 of 40 passes for 261 yards with an interception, led the Dolphins 80 yards down the field early in the fourth, a promising drive that included two fourth-down conversions. But receiver <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4569603/malik-washington\">Malik Washington</a> fumbled at the 10, and Dolphins fans began to exit Hard Rock Stadium en masse with more than 10 minutes remaining.\n\n\r\n              You want to dictate the terms. You want to fix stuff, Dolphins coach Mike McDaniel said. That sucks. All of that does. But it's a pretty consistent formula of  fans enjoy winning. Our expectation is that we have to do that work and do the right things for fans to enjoy the experience. Unfortunately we didn't do that tonight, so we've got to get back to work to give them something to cheer about.\n\n\r\n              <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4429160/de'von-achane\">De'Von Achane</a> had 14 carries for 67 yards. <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4372016/jaylen-waddle\">Jaylen Waddle</a> caught six passes for 82 yards.\n\n\r\n              The Dolphins (2-7) outgained the Ravens 226 yards to 109 and held them to 1 of 6 on third down in the first half, but Miami trailed 14-6 because of a slew of mistakes.\n\n\r\n              On Miami's second drive, rookie <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4567506/tahj-washington\">Tahj Washington</a> fumbled at the Dolphins 4, and Andrews caught a 2-yard TD from Jackson on fourth down on the Ravens' ensuing possession.\n\n\r\n              Achane led the Dolphins back down the field with runs of 19 and 22 yards, but a false start by offensive lineman <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4241217/larry-borom\">Larry Borom</a> on fourth-and-1 forced Miami to kick a field goal, which <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4243371/riley-patterson\">Riley Patterson</a> missed from 35 yards out.\n\n\r\n              The Ravens' offense answered again. Jackson escaped the grasp of linebacker <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4242975/jaelan-phillips\">Jaelan Phillips</a> and connected with <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4361050/isaiah-likely\">Isaiah Likely</a> for a 35-yard pickup, which set up Andrews' 20-yard score  aided by two Dolphins defenders running into each other in coverage  that put Baltimore ahead 14-3.\n\n\r\n              Against a good team like that, you just cant give them an inch,\" Phillips said, \"or theyll take a mile.\n\n\r\n              Miami's only points were Patterson's field goals of 49 and 43 yards.\n\n\r\n              <hl2>Good company</hl2>\r\n              Jackson became the fourth player in NFL history to throw at least four touchdown passes against the Dolphins in at least three games. Tom Brady did it five times, and <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/17102/josh-allen\">Josh Allen</a> and Drew Bledsoe both did it three times.\n\n\r\n              Jacksons' previous two such games against Miami were both of the five-TD, no-interception variety.\n\n\r\n              <hl2>Bad call?</hl2>\r\n              Just when it appeared the Dolphins were regaining momentum in the second, rookie running back Ollie Gordon was flagged for tripping on a play where it appeared that he slipped. The penalty wiped out a 36-yard catch by Waddle.\n\n\r\n              I saw a guy ... slip,\" McDaniel said, \"and he was called for intentionally tripping somebody. That's what I saw.\n\n\r\n              <hl2>Injuries</hl2>\r\n              Dolphins: Gordon (ankle), LB <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4431586/chop-robinson\">Chop Robinson</a> (concussion), S <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4240401/ifeatu-melifonwu\">Ifeatu Melifonwu</a> (toe) and CB <a href=\"http://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3943270/rasul-douglas\">Rasul Douglas</a> (toe) left with injuries.\n\n\r\n              <hl2>Up next</hl2>\r\n              Ravens: At Minnesota on Sunday, Nov. 9.\n\n\r\n              Dolphins: Host Buffalo on Nov. 9.\n\n\r\n              ------\n\n\r\n              AP NFL: <a href=\"https://apnews.com/hub/nfl\">https://apnews.com/hub/nfl</a>",
